Pasteur entered primary school in 1831.[

            ]
He was an average student in his early years, and not particularly
academic, as his interests were fishing and sketching.[18] He drew
many pastels and portraits of his parents, friends and neighbors.[

            ]
Pasteur attended secondary school at the Collège d'Arbois.[

            ] In
October 1838, he left for Paris to join the Pension Barbet, but became
homesick and returned in November.[

